    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. so basically someone else just keeps the money safe until everything is done? like a middleman to make sure nobody gets ripped off?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Exactly! The escrow agent acts as a neutral third party, ensuring that all the conditions of the house purchase are met before the funds change hands. They hold the buyer's money in a secure account, releasing it only when the seller fulfills their end of the deal, such as providing a clear title and the property being ready for the buyer. This way, both the buyer and seller can feel secure that the transaction will go smoothly, without any party getting shortchanged. It's like having a trustworthy middleman who makes sure everyone plays fair and keeps the peace!",
