    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah i get the middleman part. but is there anything i should watch out for with the funds? like are there specific risks or things that usually go wrong during the holding period?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While the escrow process is designed to protect both parties, there are still some things to keep an eye on. Here are a few potential risks or issues to be aware of:\n\n1. Delays: Sometimes, there can be delays in the closing process due to paperwork issues, inspections, or other unforeseen circumstances. This can extend the holding period for the funds and potentially cause financial strain if you need access to the money sooner than expected.\n\n2. Disputes: If there are disagreements between the buyer and seller regarding the terms of the sale, this could lead to a hold on the escrow funds until the dispute is resolved.\n\n3. Errors: Mistakes in the paperwork or communication can also cause problems. It's important to thoroughly review all documents and ensure that everything is in order before the funds are released.\n\n4. Fraud: While rare, there's always a risk of fraud, especially if you're dealing with unfamiliar parties. Make sure to do your due diligence and work with reputable professionals.\n\n5. Overdraft: If you have an account linked to the escrow funds, there's a risk of overdrawing if you don't monitor your account closely.\n\nTo minimize these risks, it's important to communicate regularly with your real estate agent, lender, and escrow agent, and to",
